    {
      "id": "944a1e23-2483-4acc-86c4-1bd5d4571dd2",
      "text": "Knowledge graphs represent a powerful way to organize and reason about information. They consist of entities (nodes) and relationships (edges) that connect these entities.",
      "segment_type": "paragraph",
      "level": 0,
      "title": null,
      "parent_id": null,
      "children_ids": [],
      "metadata": {
        "position": {
          "start": 0,
          "end": 165
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "38a2cc27-797b-4278-bd25-344e8ac89ef5",
      "text": "The process of building a knowledge graph involves several key steps: 1. Entity Extraction: Identifying important concepts, objects, or individuals mentioned in the text. 2. Relationship Extraction: Determining how these entities are connected to each other. 3. Entity Resolution: Ensuring that different mentions of the same entity are properly linked. 4. Knowledge Integration: Combining the extracted information with existing knowledge bases.",
      "segment_type": "section",
      "level": 0,
      "title": null,
      "parent_id": null,
      "children_ids": [
        "f3b55787-538e-4638-b59a-214e5570ffc0",
        "5020f5c5-bcad-43af-b6fb-98dab47c8a7d",
