            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "c65a25ba-daf5-4033-9273-4e007fcbc654",
      "text": "Various techniques can be used for knowledge extraction, ranging from rule-based approaches to deep learning models like BERT and GPT. These models have shown remarkable capabilities in understanding context and extracting structured information from unstructured text.",
      "segment_type": "paragraph",
      "level": 0,
      "title": null,
      "parent_id": null,
      "children_ids": [],
      "metadata": {
        "position": {
          "start": 584,
          "end": 835
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "d736508a-93a1-47b9-9f7f-cf5de373437d",
      "text": "When building knowledge graphs, it's important to consider issues like data quality, scalability, and domain specificity. For example, a knowledge graph for medical research would have different requirements than one for financial analysis.",
      "segment_type": "paragraph",
      "level": 0,
      "title": null,
      "parent_id": null,
      "children_ids": [],
      "metadata": {
        "position": {
          "start": 836,
          "end": 1054
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "85bda2d3-fd4b-419a-9a5b-946187b7d582",
      "text": "Some common challenges in knowledge graph construction include: - Handling ambiguity in natural language - Dealing with incomplete or contradictory information - Scaling to large volumes of data - Maintaining the graph over time as new information becomes available",
      "segment_type": "section",
      "level": 0,
      "title": null,
      "parent_id": null,
      "children_ids": [
